    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based <strong>hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced chicken thigh</strong> to the dish with the <strong>cornflour</strong> and <strong>dried oregano</strong> and cook for 2 min or until very lightly browned</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
