    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is very lightly browned add the <strong>chopped sweet potato</strong>, <strong>chicken stock mix</strong>,<strong> </strong>100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span><strong> boiled water, single soya </strong>and a very generous pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and<strong> pepper </strong>and stir everything together</p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cover with a lid and put the dish in the oven for 25-30 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the potatoes are tender</p>",
      "order": 4,
