    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once everything has been in the oven for 12 min, dust your work surface with a sprinkling of <strong>flour</strong></p><p>Roll out the<strong> puff pastry</strong> to approx. 0.5cm thickness with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> and add to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? You may need 2 trays!</p><p>Score a cross in the middle of the pastry and put it in the oven for 15 min or until puffed up and golden — this is your <strong>pie lid</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
